{"id":"64cba3c2-49cd-46a0-af25-ff6cf897ec3f","name":"The Halls of Einhorn","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\">╭⊱⋰⊱╯◦◦╰⊱⋰⊱╮<br><span style=\"color: rgb(213, 188, 133);\">You entered the palace to find your sister.</span><br>╰⊱⋰⊱╮◦◦╭⊱⋰⊱╯</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Servant User ◦◦ ANYPOV ◦◦ Multiple</em><br>Setting: Medieval | Species: Humans Only</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/dTZ2eA_59rMCwn_j2HXvN.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(213, 188, 133);\">{{user}} begins work as a new servant in the Grand Palace of Einhorn with a secret objective: to find their younger sister, Elin, who has run away.</span></p><p><br><span style=\"color: rgb(213, 188, 133);\">Backstory</span>: After a fight, Elin left for the capital, telling {{user}} she had met a knight who promised to help her secure a position at the palace. The Grand Palace is a vast and complex world of its own, impossible to search completely. {{user}}'s only lead is that the knight is a member of the palace guard.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(213, 188, 133);\">Premise</span>: While balancing their daily duties, {{user}} must navigate the subtle politics and personal entanglements among the servant class.</p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://rentry.co/halls-of-einhorn\" target=\"_blank\">The Halls of Einhorn Full Character Sheet</a></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(96, 96, 96);\"><em>The lorebooks are only visible to me. Please use the character sheet and E.K. carrd website as guides.</em></span></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/0QmQxZ6U-RML-K8da3Iov.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"></p><p><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://janitorai.co